You’d think that putting soap in the dishwasher and running it with a load would clean the inside, but that’s not the case. For today’s One Good Thing, Maxwell is showing you the quickest, easiest way to get your dishwasher ✨sparkling✨, along with two other fun facts you probably didn’t know about your machine. 

Read more at the link in bio. #OneGoodThingAtHome

node.title: 3 Things You Probably Didn't Know About Your Dishwasher

node.text: Creating a cozy bedroom where we can rest, relax, and recharge is more important than ever, and @ayeshacurry’s Small/Cool bedroom achieves  just that. “The goal for creating this bedroom retreat was to showcase how neutral, calming tones can still translate into interesting design,” she says. “We mainly focused on infusing texture rather than bold color, creating contrast through natural elements like wood and metal instead.” Explore and shop Ayesha’s space at the link in bio. #SmallCool

node.text:
@kaitlynbarclay’s East Village rental apartment features blue, green, orange, and more bold colors. 💥 “My biggest challenge was undeniably what color to paint the walls. All the advice I was given was to keep the walls light and white, but that’s just not me. I need to be surrounded by color. I sampled what felt like a thousand paint colors, and ultimately went with the hues that inspired me the most,” Kaitlyn says. Tour more of this vibrant, eclectic space at the link in our bio. 

(Image & Home: @kaitlynbarclay)

node.text:
@lexy_h_weixel’s Chicago rental is the ultimate '80s Art Deco glam spot, with its DIY murals and array of vintage finds. “I love lamps, especially lotus lamps from the ’80s, so I have three of those. I’ve really been leaning into ’80s Art Deco in general, so a lot of glam mixed with simple elegant lines,” Lexy explains. Check out the reading nook that’s an absolute blast to the past at the link in bio.

(Image & Home: @lexy_h_weixel)
